heading_context: File your company's annual accounts with Companies House
chunks.html_content: Limited liability partnerships cannot use this service - send your annual accounts directly to Companies House.
chunks.plain_content:
File your company's annual accounts with Companies House
Limited liability partnerships cannot use this service - send your annual accounts directly to Companies House.

heading_context: File your company's annual accounts with Companies House
chunks.html_content:
If you have a private limited company that does not need an auditor, you could file your company accounts through the same service as your company tax return.

You must get your accounts approved by your company directors before you file them.

Read guidance on what your annual accounts should include.

You’ll need a Companies House password and authentication code to use this service - you’ll be able to register for these if you do not have them.

Find out if you can use your accounting software to file other types of accounts to Companies House.

Contact Companies House to get help filing your company’s accounts online.
